{
  "texts": [
    "Prompt enhancement is mainly divided into two types: semantic enhancement and structural enhancement.",
    "Semantic enhancement includes robust task description and fewshot learning [6] guidance methods, with the goal of improving the accuracy and robustness of prompts toward the target task description.",
    "Constructing more robust and accurate task descriptions can help the model better understand the user's original intent, thereby reducing the risk of prompt injection attacks.",
    "On the other hand, the few-shot learning-based approach can improve the model's understanding of the task goal by providing multiple target task example samples for learning, even with limited training data.",
    "Structural enhancement includes two methods: changing the position of the prompt and using special symbols to modi-conversation partners from providing feedback in the future."
  ]
}